title: For Sale/Trade:  Saiga .223/5.56
postcontent: I have a properly converted Saiga .223/5.56 which has been refinished in KG GunKote (flat black). The gun is very accurate for an AK pattern rifle, and it also features a chrome lined barrrel (16"). Besides the bolt assembly, all the internals have been replaced with Tapco parts in order to remain 922r compliant. The gun features a G2 trigger group (polished by Dinzag Arms, the trigger pull is significantly better than standard AK's). I put a Tapco retaining plate in the gun, and the trigger guard is from Dinzag Arms. All of the holes which remained from conversion are filled with nylon plugs, also from Dinzag. The rear stock and pistol grip are by Tapco, and the gun features a tactical fore end (rail system) which also will retain a solid zero if optics are installed.
